statements: SELECT * FROM employee_benefits;
SELECT employee_id, employee_name FROM employee_benefits WHERE department = 'HR';
SELECT department, job_title FROM employee_benefits WHERE employee_name LIKE 'J%';
SELECT * FROM employee_benefits WHERE benefits_package = 'Gold';
SELECT employee_name, benefits_package FROM employee_benefits ORDER BY employee_id DESC;
SELECT * FROM employee_benefits WHERE department = 'IT' ORDER BY employee_name ASC;
SELECT employee_name, job_title FROM employee_benefits WHERE benefits_package = 'Gold' AND employee_id > 100;
SELECT COUNT(employee_id) AS total_employees, department FROM employee_benefits GROUP BY department;
SELECT * FROM employee_benefits WHERE job_title LIKE '%Manager%' OR job_title LIKE '%Director%' ORDER BY employee_id DESC;
SELECT employee_id, employee_name, benefits_package FROM employee_benefits WHERE department != 'HR' ORDER BY benefits_package ASC, employee_name DESC;
